The paper also involves the use of probability distributions to represent words in context, which is a technique commonly used in the field of machine learning and falls under the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). 

Furthermore, the paper involves the use of a deep generative model, which is a type of neural network architecture commonly used in the field of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). 

The paper also involves the use of image data as a source of learning signal, which suggests that it may also fall under the sub-category of cs.CV (Computer Vision).
